by mazarini at 2019-10-31T21:01:59Z

Not sure it's useful, but you can suppress some packages from composer.json (first column) :
```
+--------------------------+-------------+----------------------------------------+-------------+
| doctrine/doctrine-bundle | require     | doctrine/doctrine-migrations-bundle    | require     |
| symfony/asset            | require     | symfony/webpack-encore-bundle          | require     |
| symfony/console          | require     | doctrine/doctrine-bundle               | require     |
| symfony/console          | require     | doctrine/doctrine-migrations-bundle    | require     |
| symfony/console          | require     | doctrine/orm                           | require     |
| symfony/framework-bundle | require     | doctrine/doctrine-bundle               | require     |
| symfony/framework-bundle | require     | doctrine/doctrine-migrations-bundle    | require     |
| symfony/framework-bundle | require     | sensio/framework-extra-bundle          | require     |
| symfony/framework-bundle | require     | tgalopin/html-sanitizer-bundle         | require     |
| symfony/intl             | require     | symfony/form                           | require     |
| symfony/stopwatch        | require-dev | friendsofphp/php-cs-fixer              | require-dev |
| twig/twig                | require     | symfony/twig-bundle                    | require     |
| twig/twig                | require     | twig/extensions                        | require     |
+--------------------------+-------------+----------------------------------------+-------------+
```
Some versions you can up :
